Hello Scott! Try to use heading elements in order. Using heading elements in order provides a better structure to your webpage.

If the next heading size (`<h3>` in this case) is too big, you can use CSS to override the default font size. Like this:
```
h3 {
  font-size: 0.67em;
}
```

You can find the [default values for heading elements here](https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/rendering.html#sections-and-headings)

[Learn more about heading elements here](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/Heading_Elements)
